# STM32 Firmware Documentation

This directory contains the state machine implementation for the NUCLEO-G070RB development board.

## Hardware Configuration
   Microcontroller: STM32F445RE
   User Input: Tactile Switch connected to Pin `PC13` (Configured as EXTI Interrupt falling edge, Internal Pull-up).
   User Output: Green LED connected to Pin `PA5`.

## State Machine Logic
The system starts with the LED turned off. Each physical switch press advances the state cycle:
1. 1st Press: LED blinks at 0.5 Hz (Toggles every 1000ms via `TIM2`).
2. 2nd Press: LED blinks at 1 Hz (Toggles every 500ms via `TIM2`).
3. 3rd Press: LED blinks at 2 Hz (Toggles every 250ms via `TIM2`).
4. 4th Press: LED turns **OFF** completely.
5. 5th Press: Loops back to the 1st press configuration.

## Low Power Strategy
To meet the power optimization requirements for the in-person interview, the main execution loop implements the `__WFI()` (Wait For Interrupt) instruction. This stops the CPU clock and saves power, waking the processor up only when an EXTI button edge occurs or the internal `TIM2` peripheral overflows.
